This paper is about automated skin lesion analysis using deep learning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves active learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for reducing annotation cost. The paper also discusses data augmentation, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) fields. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant.
